1
00:02:22,286 --> 00:02:24,166
Are we the first?

2
00:02:26,926 --> 00:02:29,206
Are we the first to arrive here?

3
00:03:08,686 --> 00:03:10,606
Is the interpreter with you?

4
00:03:11,726 --> 00:03:16,526
I'm not a professional interpreter.
My occupation is cartography.

5
00:03:17,126 --> 00:03:18,446
I'm a mapmaker.

6
00:03:18,646 --> 00:03:21,446
Can you translate French into English
and English into French?

7
00:03:21,646 --> 00:03:24,646
Yes, I explained to the team leader in
Villa Hermosa.

8
00:03:24,846 --> 00:03:27,006
I'm just a little taken by surprise.

9
00:03:27,206 --> 00:03:30,286
-Êtes-vous MonsieurLoglin?
-Laughlin, oui.

10
00:03:30,486 --> 00:03:31,846
Oh, Laughlin. Pardon.

11
00:03:51,686 --> 00:03:54,606
They're all there! All of them!

12
00:04:05,486 --> 00:04:07,606
Check for landing marks!

13
00:04:31,526 --> 00:04:35,046
Mr. Lacombe wants the numbers
off the engine blocks!

14
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:41,006
M-447148!

15
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:45,366
W-445529!

16
00:04:45,646 --> 00:04:48,886
Number 445529, check!

17
00:04:49,126 --> 00:04:53,446
Approximately 46 gallons
in the right tank!

18
00:04:53,646 --> 00:04:55,406
447149, check!

19
00:04:55,606 --> 00:04:57,846
Tell me something.
What's happening here?

20
00:04:58,126 --> 00:05:00,366
-It's flight number 19!
-19 what?

21
00:05:00,646 --> 00:05:04,166
It's that training mission from the
naval air station at Fort Lauderdale.

22
00:05:04,646 --> 00:05:07,406
They were doing target runs
on an old hulk.

23
00:05:07,566 --> 00:05:09,846
Who flies crates like these anymore?

24
00:05:10,126 --> 00:05:14,646
No one! These planes were reported
missing in 1945.

25
00:05:19,566 --> 00:05:21,126
But it looks brand-new!

26
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:27,086
Where's the pilot?

27
00:05:27,886 --> 00:05:30,006
I don't understand!

28
00:05:30,686 --> 00:05:32,766
Where's the crew?!

29
00:05:36,606 --> 00:05:39,366
How the hell did it get here?!

30
00:06:10,726 --> 00:06:12,126
He says this guy's local.

31
00:06:12,326 --> 00:06:14,846
He was here last night.
He saw it happen.

32
00:06:36,686 --> 00:06:38,206
Sunburn?

33
00:06:53,726 --> 00:06:56,486
He says the sun came out last night.

34
00:06:57,806 --> 00:07:00,086
He says it sang to him.

35
00:07:34,886 --> 00:07:37,006
Ernie, keep an eye on that point-out.

36
00:07:37,246 --> 00:07:39,166
He's on 1 22.5.

37
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:40,806
I'll be right back.

38
00:07:42,526 --> 00:07:45,886
Indianapolis Center, you have any
traffic for Air East 31?

39
00:07:47,806 --> 00:07:48,886
Air East 31, negative.

40
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:53,846
The only traffic I have is
a TWA L-1011 in your 6:00 position...

41
00:07:54,126 --> 00:07:56,286
...range 15 miles...

42
00:07:56,726 --> 00:08:00,286
...and an Allegheny DC-9 in your 12:00
position, 50 miles.

43
00:08:00,486 --> 00:08:03,286
Stand by. I'll take a look at
broadband, over.

44
00:08:03,646 --> 00:08:07,046
Air East 31 has traffic 2:00,
slightly above and descending.

45
00:08:07,886 --> 00:08:09,166
Air East 31, roger.

46
00:08:09,406 --> 00:08:12,326
I have a primary target
about that position now.

47
00:08:12,526 --> 00:08:14,126
I have no known traffic.

48
00:08:14,326 --> 00:08:16,326
Stand by, I'll check low, over.

49
00:08:17,046 --> 00:08:19,206
Check and see if they know who it is.

50
00:08:19,406 --> 00:08:20,766
Center, Air East 31.

51
00:08:20,966 --> 00:08:22,806
The traffic's not lower than us.

52
00:08:23,046 --> 00:08:26,366
He's 1:00 now,
still above me and descending.

53
00:08:27,086 --> 00:08:29,726
Air East 31,
can you say aircraft type?

54
00:08:30,566 --> 00:08:34,086
Negative, Center, no distinct outline.

55
00:08:35,486 --> 00:08:38,086
To tell you the truth,
the target is rather brilliant.

56
00:08:38,286 --> 00:08:42,086
It has the brightest anti-collision
lights I think I've ever seen.

57
00:08:42,326 --> 00:08:44,326
Alternating white to red.

58
00:08:44,766 --> 00:08:46,326
The colors are striking.

59
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:49,606
Center, this is TWA 517.

60
00:08:49,886 --> 00:08:52,966
Traffic now looks like
extra-bright landing lights.

61
00:08:53,206 --> 00:08:56,166
I thought Air East
had his landing lights on.

62
00:08:57,406 --> 00:08:58,806
It could be a satellite.

63
00:08:59,046 --> 00:09:01,726
I have a primary target now
in your 10:00 position...

64
00:09:01,966 --> 00:09:03,166
...five miles, over.

65
00:09:03,406 --> 00:09:04,806
Affirmative, 31.

66
00:09:05,486 --> 00:09:08,766
The traffic is proceeding northeast.
No altitude readout.

67
00:09:08,966 --> 00:09:11,766
Roger, Center. It doesn't appear
he'll be a problem.

68
00:09:12,006 --> 00:09:15,206
He's going to descend
about 1500 feet below me.

69
00:09:15,406 --> 00:09:16,926
Wait a second!

70
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,366
Stand by, one.

71
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:21,766
Okay, Center, Air East 31.
The traffic has turned.

72
00:09:21,966 --> 00:09:25,286
He's heading formy windshield.
We're turning immediately.

73
00:09:27,126 --> 00:09:29,126
Descend and maintain flight level 310.

74
00:09:29,366 --> 00:09:31,166
Break Allegheny,
turn right 30 degrees.

75
00:09:31,366 --> 00:09:35,806
Get on the horn to the 45th Recon Wing
and see what they're testing up there.

76
00:09:36,046 --> 00:09:39,766
Do you have test operations
in restricted area 2508?

77
00:09:40,086 --> 00:09:41,606
Air East 31, roger.

78
00:09:41,806 --> 00:09:45,726
The traffic is luminous and
exhibiting non-ballistic motion.

79
00:09:45,926 --> 00:09:48,526
Roger. Continue descent
at your discretion.

80
00:09:48,726 --> 00:09:51,486
Okay, Center. Descent
at pilot's discretion is approved.

81
00:09:51,686 --> 00:09:54,726
The traffic is approaching head-on,
ultra-bright and really moving.

82
00:09:54,926 --> 00:09:58,286
And right by us! Right now!
Now that was really close.

83
00:09:58,486 --> 00:10:01,166
Air East 31 is out of 340....

84
00:10:01,486 --> 00:10:03,566
Ask if they want to report officially.

85
00:10:04,206 --> 00:10:07,566
TWA 517, do you want to report a UFO?
Over.

86
00:10:11,886 --> 00:10:15,366
TWA 517, do you want to report a UFO?
Over.

87
00:10:17,486 --> 00:10:20,446
Negative. We don't want to report.

88
00:10:20,646 --> 00:10:23,686
Air East 31,
do you wish to report a UFO? Over.

89
00:10:25,326 --> 00:10:27,966
Negative. We don't want
to report one either.

90
00:10:28,526 --> 00:10:32,046
Air East 31, do you wish to file a
report of any kind? Over.

91
00:10:32,806 --> 00:10:35,646
I wouldn't know what kind
of report to file, Center.

92
00:10:35,886 --> 00:10:37,766
Air East 31, me neither.

93
00:10:37,966 --> 00:10:40,206
I'll try to track traffic
to destination, over.

94
00:13:20,606 --> 00:13:21,926
Barry?

95
00:13:32,606 --> 00:13:33,766
Honey?

96
00:13:48,846 --> 00:13:50,406
Barry!

97
00:14:09,646 --> 00:14:12,526
Dad, do my problems for me.

98
00:14:13,886 --> 00:14:17,886
I don't have to do your problems for
you. You do your problems for you.

99
00:14:18,086 --> 00:14:21,566
That's why I graduated,
so I don't have to do problems.

100
00:14:21,966 --> 00:14:24,486
I don't understand these fractions.

101
00:14:24,686 --> 00:14:27,806
All right. What's one-third of 60?

102
00:14:28,526 --> 00:14:30,486
That's a fraction.
I don't understand it.

103
00:14:30,686 --> 00:14:32,006
All right, look.

104
00:14:32,366 --> 00:14:33,766
Let's say...

105
00:14:34,886 --> 00:14:38,206
...that this boxcar is 60 feet long.

106
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:42,406
And one-third is across
this switch here.

107
00:14:45,486 --> 00:14:47,726
And now another train is coming.

108
00:14:51,326 --> 00:14:54,206
How far do you have to move
this boxcar off the track...

109
00:14:54,406 --> 00:14:56,806
...so that the other train
doesn't smash it?

110
00:14:57,006 --> 00:14:59,566
Quickly, Brad, there are thousands
of lives at stake.

111
00:15:00,366 --> 00:15:02,086
Brad, any answer.

112
00:15:04,446 --> 00:15:06,406
Remember last weekend...

113
00:15:06,846 --> 00:15:10,206
...you promised everybody a movie
this weekend?

114
00:15:12,206 --> 00:15:13,446
Honey?

115
00:15:16,046 --> 00:15:18,926
And you also promised Goofy Golf.

116
00:15:24,446 --> 00:15:27,886
Roy, what is all this stuff
on my table?

117
00:15:28,366 --> 00:15:30,686
I thought I told you
this was for my stuff.

118
00:15:30,886 --> 00:15:32,766
I mean, you can have that table.

119
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:34,446
I don't want this on my table.

120
00:15:34,686 --> 00:15:36,686
This can cause tetanus!

121
00:15:37,126 --> 00:15:39,406
-What is this?!
-You know what's playing?

122
00:15:39,686 --> 00:15:42,406
Pinocchio!
The kids have never seen Pinocchio.

123
00:15:42,606 --> 00:15:45,126
You guys have never seen it.
You'll love it.

124
00:15:45,326 --> 00:15:46,526
I don't believe this.

125
00:15:46,726 --> 00:15:51,166
Who wants to go see
some dumb cartoon rated G for kids?

126
00:15:51,406 --> 00:15:53,166
-How old are you?
-Eight.

127
00:15:53,406 --> 00:15:55,046
-You want to be 9?
-Yeah.

128
00:15:55,246 --> 00:15:57,766
Then you're gonna see Pinocchio
tomorrow night.

129
00:15:58,886 --> 00:16:01,006
That's a wonderful way
to win over your children.

130
00:16:01,326 --> 00:16:05,126
I'm not serious. I'm just saying
that I grew up with Pinocchio.

131
00:16:05,326 --> 00:16:08,126
And if kids are still kids,
they're gonna eat it up.

132
00:16:10,686 --> 00:16:13,006
Okay, I'm wrong.
I'm Wrong Roy, all right?

133
00:16:13,166 --> 00:16:16,846
Toby! You are close to death!
Come out here!

134
00:16:21,646 --> 00:16:26,286
I'll give you your choice.
I'm not gonna be biased in any way.

135
00:16:26,526 --> 00:16:30,406
You can either play Goofy Golf, which
means a lot of waiting and pushing...

136
00:16:30,606 --> 00:16:32,926
...or you can see Pinocchio...

137
00:16:33,166 --> 00:16:36,646
...which is a lot of furry animals and
magic and a wonderful time.

138
00:16:37,446 --> 00:16:39,046
-Now, let's vote.
-Golf!

139
00:16:39,246 --> 00:16:40,806
All right, everybody to bed!

140
00:16:41,086 --> 00:16:44,966
No way! Dad said we could finish
watching The Ten Commandments!

141
00:16:45,926 --> 00:16:48,406
Roy, that movie is four hours long.

142
00:16:48,606 --> 00:16:51,006
I told them
they'd watch only five commandments.

143
00:16:51,246 --> 00:16:52,606
Hi, Ronnie, it's Earl.

144
00:16:52,806 --> 00:16:55,886
We got a big problem.
I need your old man in the field.

145
00:16:56,126 --> 00:16:58,046
Roy can't drive at night without me.

146
00:16:58,286 --> 00:17:00,326
We're experiencing an overall outage!

147
00:17:00,606 --> 00:17:03,406
Wait, I can't-- Honey!

148
00:17:04,046 --> 00:17:07,486
Jiminy Cricket.
It's Earl on the phone.

149
00:17:12,646 --> 00:17:16,366
Neary. Get into your truck
and report to line N in Tolono.

150
00:17:16,606 --> 00:17:20,366
We're losing power across the grid.
Has the outage hit you yet?

151
00:17:32,446 --> 00:17:33,406
Hey! Lights!

152
00:17:58,446 --> 00:18:00,806
Barry!

153
00:18:22,286 --> 00:18:24,206
Help! I'm lost.

154
00:18:26,846 --> 00:18:29,486
You're gonna cough up a little
Tolono, right?

155
00:18:29,966 --> 00:18:32,966
Cough up Tolono
on Interstate Highway 90.

156
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,566
A little familiar landmark
of some sort.

157
00:18:35,966 --> 00:18:38,566
-Cornbread Road, south of 20.
-Cornbread?

158
00:18:39,006 --> 00:18:40,606
Power must have been restored.

159
00:18:40,806 --> 00:18:43,846
Couple hundred neighbors think
it's Saturday night.

160
00:18:44,046 --> 00:18:45,126
Dispatch, this is 411.

161
00:18:45,406 --> 00:18:48,046
Do you want me to disregard
that Tolono call?

162
00:18:51,366 --> 00:18:53,286
You're in the middle of the road,
jackass!

163
00:18:53,926 --> 00:18:56,806
Can you tell me where Cornbread is?
Turkey!

164
00:19:23,846 --> 00:19:26,926
834...834.... F-27.

165
00:19:28,206 --> 00:19:31,206
M-Mary-10 through M-Mary-12. Okay.

166
00:19:38,926 --> 00:19:42,686
Stoppage in the single circuits
will lead you right to nowhere.

167
00:19:45,326 --> 00:19:46,846
M-Mary-10.

168
00:20:51,086 --> 00:20:52,086
Oh, shit!

169
00:22:39,806 --> 00:22:41,766
What do you guys got out there?

170
00:22:42,446 --> 00:22:44,206
I don't believe this!

171
00:22:44,846 --> 00:22:46,886
My God! It's as big as a house!

172
00:22:49,006 --> 00:22:50,086
Shaped like a barn.

173
00:22:51,566 --> 00:22:53,886
This is absolutely crazy.

174
00:22:58,086 --> 00:23:01,606
Just off the Telemark Expressway
and east toward Harper Valley.

175
00:24:08,366 --> 00:24:09,446
No!

176
00:24:09,806 --> 00:24:11,006
Watch out!

177
00:24:16,206 --> 00:24:18,206
Oh, my God! Lady!

178
00:24:19,046 --> 00:24:20,846
Are you okay? I'm sorry.

179
00:24:21,086 --> 00:24:24,446
I didn't see him.
He was in the middle of the road.

180
00:24:26,606 --> 00:24:28,446
Hello! Here!

181
00:24:28,646 --> 00:24:29,966
What's the matter with you?

182
00:24:30,966 --> 00:24:32,806
Barry, come back here!

183
00:25:03,686 --> 00:25:05,166
Ice cream!

184
00:25:24,526 --> 00:25:26,086
This is nuts.

185
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:09,126
Wait a minute!

186
00:26:09,886 --> 00:26:12,206
What are you guys doing? Hey!

187
00:26:12,366 --> 00:26:15,006
That's Ohio!
That's a quarter!

188
00:26:19,726 --> 00:26:23,526
Jesus, look at those suckers.
They're glued to the road!

189
00:27:09,086 --> 00:27:10,886
Honey, wake up!

190
00:27:11,566 --> 00:27:14,566
Ronnie, wake up!
You're not gonna believe what I saw!

191
00:27:14,766 --> 00:27:16,326
Don't! Not now.

192
00:27:16,606 --> 00:27:19,206
No, listen!
I never would have believed it!

193
00:27:19,406 --> 00:27:21,766
There was this--
In the cab there was this whole--

194
00:27:21,966 --> 00:27:24,526
It went-- It was-- There was a red
whoosh that--

195
00:27:26,286 --> 00:27:27,566
Roy.

196
00:27:27,766 --> 00:27:28,886
Ike called you.

197
00:27:29,646 --> 00:27:31,326
And McGovern.

198
00:27:31,646 --> 00:27:33,966
They want you to call.
They couldn't reach you.

199
00:27:34,526 --> 00:27:35,686
I turned the radio off.

200
00:27:35,966 --> 00:27:38,046
Don't do that. The phone rang
off the hook.

201
00:27:38,286 --> 00:27:41,726
It woke Sylvia up two times already.
You'd better call them.

202
00:27:41,926 --> 00:27:45,006
You know those pictures in National
Geographic, the aurora borealis?

203
00:27:45,246 --> 00:27:47,726
This is better than that. Come on!

204
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:49,806
Come on, Ronnie, get up.

205
00:27:50,046 --> 00:27:52,126
-What's wrong?
-Nothing. I don't know.

206
00:27:52,366 --> 00:27:54,606
-Get up!
-Is it an accident?

207
00:27:54,846 --> 00:27:57,606
It's not an accident.
You wanted out of the house, right?

208
00:27:57,806 --> 00:27:59,326
Not at 4:00 in the morning.

209
00:27:59,566 --> 00:28:02,886
Ronnie, I need you
to see something with me.

210
00:28:03,086 --> 00:28:04,806
It's really important.

211
00:28:05,006 --> 00:28:07,526
Okay. All right.
What about the kids?

212
00:28:07,726 --> 00:28:09,406
The kids! I'll get the kids.

213
00:28:09,646 --> 00:28:11,566
Sylvia, we're going on an adventure.

214
00:28:11,966 --> 00:28:14,406
Toby! Brad! Come on! Get up.

215
00:28:14,766 --> 00:28:16,286
It's better than Goofy Golf!

216
00:28:20,486 --> 00:28:22,766
I'm going as fast as I can!

217
00:28:23,726 --> 00:28:24,806
Come on.

218
00:28:28,006 --> 00:28:29,766
Hi, Mrs. Harris.

219
00:28:30,006 --> 00:28:31,566
Roy, there's Mrs. Harris.

220
00:28:31,766 --> 00:28:33,566
There better be a good reason
for this...

221
00:28:33,766 --> 00:28:35,166
...because it doesn't make sense!

222
00:28:36,526 --> 00:28:40,246
All right, Roy, I really think
you've proved your point.

223
00:28:43,526 --> 00:28:45,726
You're sunburned. Look at you.

224
00:28:51,566 --> 00:28:53,326
Honey, what is that?

225
00:28:58,086 --> 00:29:00,006
Roy, what did it look like?

226
00:29:01,006 --> 00:29:03,126
It was like an ice-cream cone.

227
00:29:04,966 --> 00:29:06,326
What flavor?

228
00:29:06,526 --> 00:29:07,766
Orange.

229
00:29:08,646 --> 00:29:11,046
It was orange.
It wasn't like an ice-cream cone.

230
00:29:11,366 --> 00:29:13,446
It was more like a shell.

231
00:29:13,766 --> 00:29:15,046
Like a taco?

232
00:29:15,286 --> 00:29:19,766
Was it like one of those Sara Lee
moon-shaped cookies?

233
00:29:19,966 --> 00:29:22,406
Those crescent cookies?

234
00:29:30,726 --> 00:29:33,126
Don't you think I'm taking this
really well?

235
00:29:36,526 --> 00:29:40,326
I remember coming to places like
this just to look at each other.

236
00:29:44,686 --> 00:29:46,086
Snuggle.

237
00:32:05,846 --> 00:32:09,446
I don't believe it.
I don't believe it!

238
00:32:10,206 --> 00:32:11,566
I don't believe it.

239
00:32:11,726 --> 00:32:12,726
It's the Cotopaxi.

240
00:32:12,926 --> 00:32:15,886
-Why is it here?
-Beats the shit out of me.

241
00:32:49,166 --> 00:32:51,046
Is this the bathroom?

242
00:33:08,366 --> 00:33:11,566
This is not your toy to play with
every time I turn around.

243
00:33:11,846 --> 00:33:13,526
He looks like a 50l50 Bar.

244
00:33:13,766 --> 00:33:17,206
All right, out of this house.
All of you. Out of my house.

245
00:33:17,486 --> 00:33:19,686
I'm sorry, but you're
not to play with this!

246
00:33:19,886 --> 00:33:22,446
Get out while I clean up your mess!

247
00:33:22,766 --> 00:33:24,526
Thank you very much.

248
00:33:42,286 --> 00:33:44,486
I found this overnight tanning stuff.

249
00:33:44,686 --> 00:33:48,486
I want you to spray it on half
your face, so it's all one color.

