01:04:11,046 --> 01:04:12,526
-Be quiet!
-Stop it!

507
01:04:12,726 --> 01:04:14,246
I don't understand it!

508
01:04:14,486 --> 01:04:16,846
-Neither do I.
-Get out!

509
01:04:17,126 --> 01:04:19,886
Go to your room and close the door.

510
01:04:22,806 --> 01:04:23,766
-Ronnie?
-Yes.

511
01:04:24,046 --> 01:04:28,006
I'm really scared.
I want you to help me.

512
01:04:28,366 --> 01:04:31,206
All this bullshit!
It's turning this house upside down!

513
01:04:32,046 --> 01:04:33,686
I just hate you! That's why!

514
01:04:33,966 --> 01:04:35,086
No!

515
01:04:35,726 --> 01:04:38,926
Hold me. put your arms
around me. It'll really help me.

516
01:04:39,206 --> 01:04:40,326
It'll really help me.

517
01:04:40,526 --> 01:04:43,126
Listen! Listen!
Don't you see what's happening?

518
01:04:43,686 --> 01:04:45,566
None of our friends call us anymore!

519
01:04:45,806 --> 01:04:47,886
You're out of work! You don't care!

520
01:04:48,086 --> 01:04:50,646
You're ruining us! You're ruining us!

521
01:04:51,086 --> 01:04:53,446
-Ronnie, just hold on.
-No!

522
01:04:53,646 --> 01:04:54,886
Hold on.

523
01:05:02,126 --> 01:05:05,046
Ronnie, open the door now.
Come on.

524
01:05:38,926 --> 01:05:41,846
Well, what do you know?
It's disintegrated.

525
01:05:44,846 --> 01:05:48,646
Happy birthday, you thing from
another world, you.

526
01:05:49,126 --> 01:05:50,606
Thank you!

527
01:05:57,446 --> 01:05:59,246
Well, I guess he's had enough.

528
01:06:01,646 --> 01:06:03,846
Are you going to yell at me?

529
01:06:20,326 --> 01:06:21,686
Everything's fine.

530
01:06:31,526 --> 01:06:33,486
All this stuff is coming down.

531
01:06:38,286 --> 01:06:40,886
It's all gonna be like it was.

532
01:06:48,726 --> 01:06:53,646
That's the last straw!
Now I use my secret weapon!

533
01:07:23,566 --> 01:07:27,086
Roy, I'm sorry about last night.
Roy!

534
01:07:30,006 --> 01:07:32,166
Roy, what are you doing?

535
01:07:33,166 --> 01:07:34,606
Jesus!

536
01:07:43,566 --> 01:07:44,806
The plants are fine there!

537
01:07:46,126 --> 01:07:47,366
Can you hear me?

538
01:07:47,926 --> 01:07:49,046
Wait!

539
01:07:49,326 --> 01:07:51,206
Wait! What are you doing?

540
01:07:51,406 --> 01:07:52,486
You're gonna love it!

541
01:07:52,686 --> 01:07:55,046
-What do you mean?
-You'll really love this.

542
01:07:55,246 --> 01:07:57,806
Roy, what are you doing?

543
01:08:03,086 --> 01:08:04,686
Oh, Roy!

544
01:08:05,646 --> 01:08:06,486
My God!

545
01:08:08,046 --> 01:08:09,486
Come on, men!

546
01:08:10,926 --> 01:08:14,926
Dad, after this, can we
throw dirt in my window?

547
01:08:18,406 --> 01:08:19,686
Stop it.

548
01:08:20,846 --> 01:08:22,566
Stop. Stop it.

549
01:08:22,766 --> 01:08:24,086
Honey!

550
01:08:24,686 --> 01:08:28,846
lf I don't do this, that's when
I'm gonna need a doctor.

551
01:08:32,526 --> 01:08:33,366
What are you doing?

552
01:08:33,646 --> 01:08:35,206
-I got it.
-What are you doing?

553
01:08:35,406 --> 01:08:38,726
I figured it out, that's all.
Will you just listen?

554
01:08:38,926 --> 01:08:43,726
You ever look at something crazy, and
then see it another way and it's not?

555
01:08:43,926 --> 01:08:44,806
No, I haven't.

556
01:08:45,006 --> 01:08:46,966
Come on, Ronnie. Just listen.

557
01:08:47,206 --> 01:08:49,446
-I don't know what you're doing.
-Close your eyes.

558
01:08:49,646 --> 01:08:52,646
Close your eyes and hold your breath,
everything will be really pretty.

559
01:08:54,086 --> 01:08:55,046
You're scaring us now.

560
01:08:55,246 --> 01:08:58,246
Don't be scared. Don't be scared.
I feel really good.

561
01:08:58,486 --> 01:09:00,166
Everything's gonna be all right.

562
01:09:00,366 --> 01:09:02,406
I haven't felt this good in years.

563
01:09:02,606 --> 01:09:04,686
Everything's gonna be okay.
I can feel it.

564
01:09:07,926 --> 01:09:10,646
-Now what else? What else?
-Like this? Like this?

565
01:09:11,886 --> 01:09:13,126
Right.

566
01:09:50,486 --> 01:09:51,726
Like this?

567
01:09:54,486 --> 01:09:55,846
Chicken wire.

568
01:10:05,966 --> 01:10:07,846
Whatever you're doing,
it's against the law!

569
01:10:08,046 --> 01:10:09,606
He's putting it back, Mrs. Harris.

570
01:10:09,806 --> 01:10:10,886
I'll pay you for this.

571
01:10:11,086 --> 01:10:12,046
Take it. Take it.

572
01:10:12,206 --> 01:10:13,926
I'm perfectly fine.

573
01:10:14,166 --> 01:10:16,166
Let go of this fence.
Come with me.

574
01:10:16,406 --> 01:10:19,126
Do you want me to hit you?
Let go of that fence!

575
01:10:19,366 --> 01:10:21,606
Toby! Listen to me. Listen to me.

576
01:10:21,806 --> 01:10:23,526
Come on, right now.
We're going.

577
01:10:23,726 --> 01:10:26,726
-I want to stay here!
-Let go of the fence! Come on.

578
01:10:44,206 --> 01:10:45,366
Stay!

579
01:10:50,126 --> 01:10:52,486
-Where we going?
-Where we going?

580
01:10:52,686 --> 01:10:54,086
-Where are we going?
-Just get in the car.

581
01:10:54,446 --> 01:10:57,286
-Where are we going?
-Quietly, quickly, get in.

582
01:10:57,646 --> 01:10:58,806
Get in there, Toby.

583
01:10:59,366 --> 01:11:00,246
Quickly.

584
01:11:03,246 --> 01:11:05,646
-Dad needs some more help!
-Lock the doors!

585
01:11:05,806 --> 01:11:07,086
Dad needs some more help!

586
01:11:07,286 --> 01:11:09,166
Quiet! Just lock the doors.

587
01:11:09,326 --> 01:11:10,606
Roll up those windows.

588
01:11:10,886 --> 01:11:13,246
Dad needs some more help!

589
01:11:13,526 --> 01:11:15,006
Honey, where you going?

590
01:11:15,246 --> 01:11:17,046
-What?
-Where are you going?

591
01:11:17,846 --> 01:11:20,166
Taking the kids to my sister's.

592
01:11:21,526 --> 01:11:23,686
That's crazy.
You're not even dressed.

593
01:11:24,726 --> 01:11:25,766
What?

594
01:11:26,126 --> 01:11:27,526
You said what?

595
01:11:32,246 --> 01:11:33,846
Ronnie, wait!

596
01:11:34,126 --> 01:11:36,006
Ronnie, hold it.

597
01:11:37,486 --> 01:11:38,806
Will you hold it one minute?

598
01:12:05,126 --> 01:12:05,926
Morning.

599
01:12:43,886 --> 01:12:46,886
What is wrong with me today?

600
01:12:52,726 --> 01:12:53,926
Who is it, please?

601
01:12:54,286 --> 01:12:58,406
It's the mailman. There's a package
for Julie Anderson.

602
01:13:01,326 --> 01:13:04,246
You can just leave it at the door!

603
01:13:05,846 --> 01:13:10,006
I can't do that.
I'm supposed to C.O.D.

604
01:13:10,246 --> 01:13:11,526
And besides...

605
01:13:12,486 --> 01:13:14,766
...you and I have to have
a little talk...

606
01:13:15,726 --> 01:13:17,286
...about Kim.

607
01:13:35,926 --> 01:13:38,766
Like sands through the hourglass...

608
01:13:38,966 --> 01:13:41,446
...so are the Days of Our Lives.

609
01:13:43,686 --> 01:13:46,726
Here comes the king
Here comes the big number one

610
01:13:48,046 --> 01:13:51,046
Budweiser beer
The king is second to none

611
01:13:51,246 --> 01:13:54,446
When you say Bud
The king is coming

612
01:13:54,646 --> 01:13:56,166
Let's hear the call

613
01:13:56,686 --> 01:13:58,606
When you say Bud
You've said it all

614
01:13:58,806 --> 01:14:01,646
When you say Bud
You've said it all

615
01:14:06,566 --> 01:14:10,166
Good evening. At the top of the news
tonight, a rail disaster.

616
01:14:10,406 --> 01:14:12,166
At Devil's Tower, Wyoming...

617
01:14:12,366 --> 01:14:15,686
...a trainload of dangerous
chemical gas went off the rails...

618
01:14:15,886 --> 01:14:18,446
...and forced the widest
area evacuation...

619
01:14:18,646 --> 01:14:21,766
...in the history of these
controversial rail shipments.

620
01:14:21,966 --> 01:14:25,126
Whenever you want me to.
Tomorrow is fine.

621
01:14:27,046 --> 01:14:29,046
I can do other things.

622
01:14:29,766 --> 01:14:31,886
I'm trying to be.

623
01:14:33,326 --> 01:14:34,166
Yes, I am.

624
01:14:34,446 --> 01:14:37,206
The Army and National Guard are
supervising the evacuation.

625
01:14:37,646 --> 01:14:41,926
I am an adult, okay?
Even though there's no such thing.

626
01:14:42,126 --> 01:14:43,686
It was a joke!

627
01:14:43,886 --> 01:14:46,566
--the danger will be over
within 72 hours.

628
01:14:47,126 --> 01:14:49,806
Ronnie, anything you want.

629
01:14:50,126 --> 01:14:52,646
Anything you want, I'll do.

630
01:14:55,566 --> 01:14:56,966
For how long?

631
01:15:02,726 --> 01:15:04,246
All of you?

632
01:15:05,526 --> 01:15:09,926
No. Ronnie, I want to talk
about this in person.

633
01:15:10,926 --> 01:15:14,326
This is not-- We can't talk
about this on the telephone.

634
01:15:15,726 --> 01:15:19,606
Ronnie! Don't hang up!
Just don't--

635
01:15:24,486 --> 01:15:27,486
Devil's Tower, Wyoming was
the first national monument...

636
01:15:27,686 --> 01:15:31,286
...erected in this country by
Theodore Roosevelt in 1915.

637
01:15:31,566 --> 01:15:34,846
Thousands of civilian refugees
are fleeing the area...

638
01:15:35,086 --> 01:15:38,366
...spurred by rumors that the
overturned tanker cars...

639
01:15:38,606 --> 01:15:42,886
...at Walkashi Needles Junction were
filled to capacity with nerve gas.

640
01:15:48,406 --> 01:15:51,286
Fortunately,
there have been no fatalities.

641
01:15:51,526 --> 01:15:53,646
--evacuate this area,
which soon...

642
01:15:53,926 --> 01:15:57,446
...will become the "hot zone,"
depending on the prevailing winds.

643
01:15:57,646 --> 01:16:01,286
This is as close to the disaster
as we've been allowed to get.

644
01:16:01,526 --> 01:16:04,046
--due to a strong prevailing
north-south wind.

645
01:16:04,246 --> 01:16:06,926
Army engineers and the
Wyoming National Guard...

646
01:16:07,126 --> 01:16:10,566
...are making every effort to
contain the leaking toxins...

647
01:16:10,766 --> 01:16:13,766
...and evacuate an area of almost
200 square miles.

648
01:16:13,966 --> 01:16:17,166
Everyone is being warned:
Stay out of the area.

649
01:16:17,486 --> 01:16:20,166
Everyone, please,
stay out of the area.

650
01:16:20,526 --> 01:16:22,446
--thousands of others
are homeless.

651
01:16:22,646 --> 01:16:26,926
U.S. Army Materiel Command has
issued these new area restrictions:

652
01:16:27,126 --> 01:16:30,406
All roadways north of Crowheart on
Interstate 25.

653
01:16:30,606 --> 01:16:33,806
All roads leading into the
Grand Tetons west of Meteste.

654
01:16:34,006 --> 01:16:36,846
All multilane undivided
full traffic interchange...

655
01:16:37,006 --> 01:16:40,806
...railroad, local and historic
stage roads south of Cody.

656
01:16:50,726 --> 01:16:53,486
Why aren't there fat lines
instead of these thin ones?

657
01:16:57,806 --> 01:16:59,686
You're going the wrong way!

658
01:17:01,646 --> 01:17:04,726
Turn back around. Back this way.

659
01:17:05,366 --> 01:17:06,806
What's the matter with you?

660
01:17:07,086 --> 01:17:08,606
Yes, sir. Sorry, officer.

661
01:17:08,846 --> 01:17:11,526
It's just a rental, officer.

662
01:17:12,326 --> 01:17:13,606
My fault! My fault!

663
01:17:13,806 --> 01:17:16,006
Starting with the letter "F,"
as in "Frank"...

664
01:17:16,326 --> 01:17:18,326
...to the letter "J" as in "Jack"...

665
01:17:18,566 --> 01:17:22,726
...please find your way to the loading
platform for immediate boarding.

666
01:17:26,246 --> 01:17:28,486
You'll be real disappointed
and sorry...

667
01:17:28,686 --> 01:17:32,966
...if you don't have an early warning
system, such as a bird, a gas mask.

668
01:17:33,166 --> 01:17:35,206
Why, even my dog has a gas mask.

669
01:17:35,446 --> 01:17:37,966
And any of you folks are
worth more than a dog.

670
01:18:08,366 --> 01:18:09,846
Roy!

671
01:18:21,166 --> 01:18:24,046
I don't care where you go,
just get behind the barricade!

672
01:18:49,806 --> 01:18:50,806
Why are we here?

673
01:18:51,046 --> 01:18:54,246
The only way there is across country.
We'll break through the fence.

674
01:18:54,446 --> 01:18:56,206
-Let's go.
-All right, hold on.

675
01:19:19,366 --> 01:19:21,606
The police dragged the river for him.

676
01:19:21,806 --> 01:19:24,646
I told them he wasn't in the river.
He wasn't.

677
01:19:24,846 --> 01:19:29,326
Then they went around to every house
within five miles...

678
01:19:30,286 --> 01:19:34,166
...looking inside backyard
refrigerators.

679
01:19:38,086 --> 01:19:41,286
They asked if I'd seen any strangers
in the neighbourhood.

680
01:20:46,606 --> 01:20:48,806
I don't believe it's real.

681
01:20:50,806 --> 01:20:52,806
I don't believe it's real!

682
01:20:53,966 --> 01:20:55,406
It's real.

683
01:21:01,686 --> 01:21:04,806
Let's get down there. Get some gas
and get down in there.

684
01:21:07,926 --> 01:21:08,886
What are those?

685
01:21:32,366 --> 01:21:36,326
Look, I guarantee you.
This whole thing is a put-on.

686
01:22:21,326 --> 01:22:23,566
What do you want?
Get your hands off!

687
01:22:25,766 --> 01:22:28,046
-How are you feeling?
-I feel fine!

688
01:22:28,726 --> 01:22:31,926
According to my birds, the bad air
is from you guys farting around!

689
01:22:42,646 --> 01:22:44,486
-Move them out!
-What's happening?

690
01:22:44,686 --> 01:22:46,406
Where are we going?

691
01:22:47,046 --> 01:22:48,366
Where are you taking her?

692
01:22:48,566 --> 01:22:50,726
Hold it! Why can't we go together?

693
01:22:50,926 --> 01:22:51,686
Watch your step.

694
01:23:09,286 --> 01:23:12,966
We have very little time, Mr. Neary.
This is Mr. Lacombe.

695
01:23:13,206 --> 01:23:16,646
We need answers from you that are
honest, direct and to the point.

696
01:23:16,846 --> 01:23:17,926
Where is Jillian?

697
01:23:20,166 --> 01:23:23,126
Do you realize the danger you
and your friend have risked?

698
01:23:24,166 --> 01:23:27,286
In coming here, you've
exposed yourself to toxic gas.

699
01:23:27,566 --> 01:23:29,006
Well, I'm alive.

700
01:23:29,206 --> 01:23:30,566
We're talking.

701
01:23:31,566 --> 01:23:33,486
This is true, Mr. Neary.

702
01:23:34,326 --> 01:23:37,606
But if the wind blew from
the south instead of the north...

703
01:23:38,926 --> 01:23:41,046
...this conversation would not be
taking place.

704
01:23:41,286 --> 01:23:43,046
There's nothing wrong with the air.

705
01:23:44,526 --> 01:23:46,006
What makes you say that?

706
01:23:46,286 --> 01:23:48,406
I just know.
There's nothing wrong with it.

707
01:23:48,966 --> 01:23:51,046
Go outside and make me a liar.

708
01:23:55,086 --> 01:23:57,446
I want to talk to the man in charge.

709
01:23:57,646 --> 01:23:59,886
Mr. Lacombe is the highest authority.

710
01:24:00,246 --> 01:24:02,006
He isn't even an American.

711
01:24:04,326 --> 01:24:07,126
Mr. Neary, are you an artist
or a painter?

712
01:24:08,366 --> 01:24:09,286
No.

713
01:24:12,726 --> 01:24:15,686
Have you been hearing a persistent
ringing in your ears?

714
01:24:15,886 --> 01:24:17,646
Almost an agreeable ringing?

715
01:24:17,846 --> 01:24:18,846
No.

716
01:24:20,206 --> 01:24:22,286
Having headaches, migraines?

717
01:24:22,766 --> 01:24:23,806
Yeah.

718
01:24:25,006 --> 01:24:26,966
An irritation in your eyes
and your sinuses?

719
01:24:27,246 --> 01:24:28,326
Yeah.

720
01:24:29,366 --> 01:24:32,486
Do you have hives?
Do you have allergies?

721
01:24:34,446 --> 01:24:36,646
And burning on your face
and on your body?

722
01:24:36,846 --> 01:24:39,286
-Yes. Who are you people?
-Look at this.

723
01:24:39,566 --> 01:24:42,446
I got one like it in my living room.
Who are you?

724
01:24:48,046 --> 01:24:50,446
Monsieur Neary, please,
one more question.

725
01:24:52,166 --> 01:24:54,646
Have you recently had
a close encounter?

726
01:24:55,726 --> 01:24:58,726
A close encounter
with something very unusual?

727
01:25:01,526 --> 01:25:03,406
Who are you people?

728
01:25:09,806 --> 01:25:13,646
-These people strangers to you?
-Yeah. Except for her.

729
01:25:15,726 --> 01:25:18,446
And the two of you felt compelled
to be here?

730
01:25:19,566 --> 01:25:21,366
Yeah, you might say that.

731
01:25:21,806 --> 01:25:24,966
-But what did you expect to find?
-An answer.

732
01:25:26,566 --> 01:25:28,366
That's not crazy, is it?

733
01:25:43,926 --> 01:25:46,806
Hold it, hold it, hold it.

734
01:25:47,086 --> 01:25:48,206
Is that it?

735
01:25:49,166 --> 01:25:51,526
Is that all you're going to ask me?

736
01:25:52,366 --> 01:25:54,726
I got a couple of thousand
goddamn questions.

737
01:25:54,926 --> 01:25:58,966
I want to speak to someone in charge.
I want to lodge a complaint.

738
01:25:59,366 --> 01:26:01,526
You have no right to make people crazy.

739
01:26:01,766 --> 01:26:05,766
You think I investigate every
Walter Cronkite story there is?

740
01:26:06,166 --> 01:26:09,686
lf this is just nerve gas, how come I
know everything in such detail?

741
01:26:09,926 --> 01:26:11,606
I've never been here before.

742
01:26:12,526 --> 01:26:14,326
How come I know so much?

743
01:26:14,646 --> 01:26:16,486
What the hell is going on
around here?!

744
01:26:16,686 --> 01:26:18,646
Who the hell are you people?!

745
01:26:42,446 --> 01:26:44,486
Is that it?! Answer me!

746
01:26:45,166 --> 01:26:48,486
I didn't come this far to get
taken on any bus ride home!

747
01:27:10,126 --> 01:27:12,086
Five minutes. Five!

748
01:27:12,726 --> 01:27:14,886
We're gonna hold
for a couple of minutes.

749
01:27:47,446 --> 01:27:50,606
You brought 12 people to
the decontamination camp...

750
01:27:50,806 --> 01:27:55,046
...instead of the evacuation centre
where they belong. Why?

751
01:27:55,246 --> 01:27:57,966
-Because this means something.
-This means something.

752
01:27:59,766 --> 01:28:02,886
These people have come from
all over their country...

753
01:28:04,646 --> 01:28:07,846
...to a place they've been told
will endanger their lives.

754
01:28:08,046 --> 01:28:09,126
Why?

755
01:28:09,366 --> 01:28:12,966
Because somebody could be trying
